What: “Another tweet in the wall” is your guide to understand the evolving border barrier narrative targeted by President Trump’s political regime

Why: Attempts at curbing cross-border migration to fuel political agendas has been a peculiar phenomenon of the rising authoritarian regimes. The basis to do so are however normative. This is an attempt at addressing the information asymmetry (or gaps) that bridges the gap between citizens and the given political crisis around the border barrier aka “The Wall”  that separates Mexico from the USA. We also aim to highlight the influence of Trump’s twitter activity in inciting hate speech, discrimination or his use of power to influence the masses.

How: 
Analyze his tweets from the beginning of his campaign to the present day
Identify key words that cater to discrimination and or hatred or exclusion
Look at the retweets and the twitter activity by month and year

